  "detailed_description": "<h1>Unity's Creator Spotlight</h1><p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Join Unity’s Creator Spotlight on YouTube on Thursday, January 30th, at 6 PM CET!</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Cat Detective Albert Wilde will be discussed by Maria, Andreas, and Jackson as we dive into the technical and creative elements of the game.</p></p><br><h1>About the Game</h1><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1810670/extras/c286f221aa3ba53dfdd351bdcacad79b.poster.avif?t=1757097191\" width=616 height=250 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1810670/extras/c286f221aa3ba53dfdd351bdcacad79b.webm?t=1757097191\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1810670/extras/c286f221aa3ba53dfdd351bdcacad79b.mp4?t=1757097191\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Cat Detective Albert Wilde</strong> is a 1930s noir-inspired detective game with humanoid animal characters. </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >How does Albert Wilde solve the strangest quantum mystery in a murder case? </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Find out in this 6-7 hours silly and hilarious classic detective adventure tribute to the golden age of noir movies</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1810670/extras/dea827a3e7c40a29ef0967b12ea797e9.webp?t=1757097191\" width=616 height=60 /></span>Use your years of experience of interrogating and drinking at bars to chat with locals to solve a mystery. Rely on your cat-charisma to find the truth.  </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1810670/extras/9287497e11fba62815f9022be897e273.webp?t=1757097191\" width=616 height=60 /></span>Meet a cast of 27 interesting characters like a pole-dancing flamingo, a piggy lawyer, a pissed-off moose bookie, an out-of-tune sheep singer, a FAMOUS SCIENTIST and the dangerous crocodile gang. </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1810670/extras/64efed43512bc1ab0eb45738d9859a1b.webp?t=1757097191\" width=616 height=60 /></span>Albert Wilde is down on his luck. He’s broke, he’s friendless, he can’t get a girl, and his landlord won’t let him pee on the office wall anymore.  </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1810670/extras/65e24d442b7984448b1a5d45959d9ce5.poster.avif?t=1757097191\" width=616 height=250 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1810670/extras/65e24d442b7984448b1a5d45959d9ce5.webm?t=1757097191\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1810670/extras/65e24d442b7984448b1a5d45959d9ce5.mp4?t=1757097191\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Q & A</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Is the game a combination of different genres?</strong></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Yes, it’s hard to define <i>Cat Detective Albert Wilde</i> by a single genre, as we tend to blend multiple elements in our projects. This game is a fusion of comedy, film noir, detective mystery, science fiction, and narrative. </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Can you describe the genre from a technical perspective?</strong></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >From a technical perspective, you could describe it as something between a walking simulator and an interactive novel, with a strong emphasis on comedy. </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Is this game a kind of ‘whodunnit’ murder mystery game? </strong></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >It’s less of a typical \"whodunnit\" and more of an origin story—showing how Albert Wilde evolves from a Private Investigator (P.I.) to a Quantum Private Investigator.</p>",
  "about_the_game": "<p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1810670/extras/c286f221aa3ba53dfdd351bdcacad79b.poster.avif?t=1757097191\" width=616 height=250 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1810670/extras/c286f221aa3ba53dfdd351bdcacad79b.webm?t=1757097191\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1810670/extras/c286f221aa3ba53dfdd351bdcacad79b.mp4?t=1757097191\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Cat Detective Albert Wilde</strong> is a 1930s noir-inspired detective game with humanoid animal characters. </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >How does Albert Wilde solve the strangest quantum mystery in a murder case? </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Find out in this 6-7 hours silly and hilarious classic detective adventure tribute to the golden age of noir movies</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1810670/extras/dea827a3e7c40a29ef0967b12ea797e9.webp?t=1757097191\" width=616 height=60 /></span>Use your years of experience of interrogating and drinking at bars to chat with locals to solve a mystery. Rely on your cat-charisma to find the truth.  </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1810670/extras/9287497e11fba62815f9022be897e273.webp?t=1757097191\" width=616 height=60 /></span>Meet a cast of 27 interesting characters like a pole-dancing flamingo, a piggy lawyer, a pissed-off moose bookie, an out-of-tune sheep singer, a FAMOUS SCIENTIST and the dangerous crocodile gang. </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1810670/extras/64efed43512bc1ab0eb45738d9859a1b.webp?t=1757097191\" width=616 height=60 /></span>Albert Wilde is down on his luck. He’s broke, he’s friendless, he can’t get a girl, and his landlord won’t let him pee on the office wall anymore.  </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1810670/extras/65e24d442b7984448b1a5d45959d9ce5.poster.avif?t=1757097191\" width=616 height=250 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1810670/extras/65e24d442b7984448b1a5d45959d9ce5.webm?t=1757097191\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1810670/extras/65e24d442b7984448b1a5d45959d9ce5.mp4?t=1757097191\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Q & A</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Is the game a combination of different genres?</strong></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Yes, it’s hard to define <i>Cat Detective Albert Wilde</i> by a single genre, as we tend to blend multiple elements in our projects. This game is a fusion of comedy, film noir, detective mystery, science fiction, and narrative. </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Can you describe the genre from a technical perspective?</strong></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >From a technical perspective, you could describe it as something between a walking simulator and an interactive novel, with a strong emphasis on comedy. </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Is this game a kind of ‘whodunnit’ murder mystery game? </strong></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >It’s less of a typical \"whodunnit\" and more of an origin story—showing how Albert Wilde evolves from a Private Investigator (P.I.) to a Quantum Private Investigator.</p>",
